The paper discusses a neural network model (GBNN) and its use as an associative memory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the paper proposes heuristics and a post-processing algorithm to improve the performance of the model, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of sparse encoding and resilience to noise also suggests that the paper may belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the convergence properties of the model, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT).
